title: My phone failed to send or receive a multimedia message. Why? What can I do?
answer:
>Multimedia messages cannot be received if you do not have sufficient storage available on your phone. To solve this problem, delete unnecessary files to increase your phone's available storage space.   

>Multimedia messages cannot be sent or received if data services are disabled. To solve this problem, touch > System settings > MoreÂ¡K > Mobile networks, and select Data enabled.
